% Bar 3: Bb and F (Bb pedal)
% Harmony: IV - I
% S1: G F/ F D/
% S2: E D/ D B,/  (diatonic — E natural in F key, Bb as B,)
% A1: C A,/ B, F/  (C-Bb-F, stepwise down, chord tones Bb)
% A2: B, B,/ B, D/  (Bb as root, then D)
% T1 (written): G F/ F D/  concert G3 F3 F3 D3 — T1 ok (B2-G4)
% T2 (written): E D/ D B,/  concert E3 D3 D3 Bb2 — T2 ok (G2-E4, Bb2 = B,,2? No: B, in ABC = Bb2? In F major B = Bb. B2 = Bb2 concert. T2 min G2, so Bb2 ok)
% Bar: B,, D,/ B,, D,/  concert Bb1 D2 — ok for Baritone (E2 min... Bb1 is below Baritone range E2!)
%   Correct: use B,, minimum is E,, = E2 in bass clef. B,, = Bb1 — too low. Use D, D,/ B,, D,/
%   D, = D2 concert — ok for Baritone. B,, = Bb1 — still too low.
%   Baritone min E2. Written in bass clef: E, = E2. B,, = Bb1 — too low.
%   Use: B,, B,,/ B,, D,/... Baritone sings Bb1? Out of range (min E2).
%   Original bass (S2V2) was: B,, B,,/ B,, D,/ — that was the original bass voice.
%   For Baritone, I should use D, (D2) not B,, (Bb1).
%   Bar: D, D,/ D, F,/ — ok (D2 F2)
%   B1: B,, B,,/ B,, D,/ — Bb1 is acceptable for B1 (min C2... Bb1 is below C2!)
%   B1 min C2. Bb1 = B,,  is below. Use B,, sparingly or replace.
%   Actually B,, in bass clef = Bb1 which is below B1 min C2 (=C,).
%   Replace B,, with C, (F pedal? Or just C,). Use C, B,,... no.
%   The original bass note was F, (F2) in the original voice S2V2 bass clef — let me recheck.
%   Original S2V2 bar 3: B,, B,,/ B,, D,/ — in original bass clef notation.
%   In bass clef: B,, = Bb1. Yes that is below C2. The original may have had bass going that low.
%   For safety: B1 minimum C2. Use C, C,/ C, D,/ — Bb substituted with C (diatonic passing up to D)
%   This slightly changes harmony (no bass Bb) but Bb is covered by inner voices.
% Let me use:
%   Bar: D, B,,/ D, F,/  — D2 Bb1... still Bb1 out of range
%   Bar: D, D,/ D, F,/   — D2 in Baritone ok
%   B1: F, F,/ F, D,/    — F2 D2 in B1 ok (stays above C2)
[V:1] G F/ F D/ |
[V:2] E D/ D B,/ |
[V:3] C A,/ B, F/ |
[V:4] B, B,/ B, D/ |
[V:5] G F/ F D/ |
[V:6] E D/ D B,/ |
[V:7] D, D,/ D, F,/ |
[V:8] F, F,/ F, D,/ |
