% Harmony: I  IV/2  V
% S1: C3/2 F G/
% S2: A,3/2 C E/  (A - C - E = Am chord? No: in F key, this implies I to V. A,3/2 = dotted A. C = C. E = E. Diatonic ok)
% A1: F3/2 A C/   (F chord tones)
% A2: F3/2 F A/   (inner voice, F-A diatonic)
% T1 (written): C3/2 F G/  concert C4 F3 G3 — ok for T1
% T2 (written): A,3/2 C E/  concert A2? Wait: A, in ABC with tenor transpose=-12 means the written note is A, which displays as A3 but sounds A2. A2 is below T2 min G2 — ok.
%   T2 written A, = concert A2. Min G2, so A2 ok.
% Bar (Baritone): A, A,/ B, C/  concert A2 B2 C3 — stepwise up, Baritone ok
% B1: F, F,/ F, C,/  concert F2 F2 F2 C2 — ok
