% Bar 6: F and Bb
% Harmony: I  IV
% S1: d c/ A F/
% S2: B A/ F D/  (third below, diatonic Bb = B in F key)
% A1: F F/ F A/  (oblique then up)
% A2: D D/ C D/  (passing motion contrary to A1)
% T1 (written): B, C/ C C/  concert Bb2 C3 C3 C3 — ok for T1
% T2 (written): G, A,/ A, A,/  concert G2 A2 A2 A2 — ok
% Bar: D, D,/ D, F,/  concert D2 F2 — ok
% B1: B,, A,,/ F, A,,/  concert Bb1 Ab1?? Ab1 not in key — use B,, A,,/ F,, A,,/ — A,, = Ab1 below range
%   Original bass: B, A,/ F, A,,/ — B, = Bb2, A, = A2, F, = F2, A,, = Ab1. Ab1 is below range AND not diatonic (Ab not in F major).
%   In F major: A = A natural. A,, = A1 (below bass clef ledger — too low and out of range for B1 min C2)
%   Replace: B1 uses B,, = Bb1? Min C2 for B1. Bb1 below.
%   Use: B, A,/ F, C,/  — Bb2 A2 F2 C2 — all within B1 range (C2-A3). ✓
%   Actually A,, in ABC bass clef = A1 (below C2) is below range. Replace A,, with C, (C2). Stepwise: F, C,/ = F2 C2, big leap down. Or F, F,/ = oblique. Let's use:
%   B1: B, A,/ F, F,/  — Bb2 A2 F2 F2 — all ok.
% Bar: D, D,/ D, F,/  — D2 F2 — ok for Baritone (min E2, so D2 = below!)
%   Baritone min E2. D2 = D, in bass clef = too low.
%   Use F, F,/ A, F,/ — F2 A2 F2 — Baritone ok (E2-C4 range: F2 ok)
