% ===== REFRAIN =====
% Texture: Full 8-voice homophony; climax of piece.
% Bb chord throughout refrain bars 1-2.
%
% Refrain Bar 1: Bb
% S1: F/ B B B/   (original melody — F pickup then three Bb's, high point!)
% S2: D/ G G G/   (third below, diatonic: D below F, G below Bb — diatonic ok)
% A1: B,/ D D D/  (Bb chord tone D, inner voice)
% A2: F,/ B, B, B,/  (root of Bb)
% T1 (written): B,/ F, F, F,/  concert Bb2 F2 F2 F2 — ok
% T2 (written): G,/ D, D, D,/  concert G2 D2 D2 D2 — T2 ok (D2 > G2? D2 below G2! D2 is below min G2)
%   T2 written D, = concert D2 — too low. Use G,/ G, G, G,/ oblique — concert G2 ok
% Bar: B,,/ B,, B,, B,,/  concert Bb1 — Baritone min E2! Way too low. Use D,/ D, D, D,/  concert D2 — ok (E2 min... D2 still below)
%   Baritone min E2. D2 below. Use F,/ F, F, F,/  concert F2 — ok ✓
% B1: B,,/ B,, B,, B,,/  concert Bb1 — B1 min C2. Bb1 below. Use F,,/ F,, F,, F,,/... F,, = F1 even lower!
%   Original bass was Bb as root. For B1 use B,/ B, B, B,/  concert Bb2 — ok (C2 min; Bb2 = B, in bass clef = Bb2, which is above C2 ✓)
%   B, in ABC bass clef = Bb2 (one ledger below bass staff in F key)
%   Actually in F major key signature: B = Bb. So B, in bass clef = Bb2 (concert). C2 minimum for B1. Bb2 is above C2. ✓
[V:1] F/ B B B/ |
[V:2] D/ G G G/ |
[V:3] B,/ D D D/ |
[V:4] F,/ B, B, B,/ |
[V:5] B,/ F, F, F,/ |
[V:6] G,/ G, G, G,/ |
[V:7] F,/ F, F, F,/ |
[V:8] B,/ B, B, B,/ |
%
% Refrain Bar 2: Bb (sustained)
% S1: B/ d2 d/   (Bb to D, high!)
